    <!-- Add Activity -->
     <activity>
        <p>
            <alert>In Groups, study and explore the following sequence</alert>
        </p>
        <p>
            <m>3,7,11,15 ...</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            Find the next three terms of the sequence?<!--, What is the formula for getting the <m>n^{th} term?</m>--> Share with other groups your findings.
        </p>
        <p>
            The next term is obtained by adding <m>4</m> to the preceeding term. <m>4</m> is called the common difference (<m>d</m>) of the sequence. This is the difference betweeen any two consecutive terms of the sequence.
        </p>
     </activity>

